[{"text": "I want to address the issue of compassion.", "start": 15.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Compassion has many faces.", "start": 18.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Some of them are fierce; some of them are wrathful;", "start": 21.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "some of them are tender; some of them are wise.", "start": 24.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A line that the Dalai Lama once said,", "start": 27.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "he said, \"Love and compassion are necessities.", "start": 30.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They are not luxuries.", "start": 33.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Without them,", "start": 36.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "humanity cannot survive.\"", "start": 38.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I would suggest,", "start": 40.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it is not only humanity that won't survive,", "start": 42.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but it is all species on the planet,", "start": 45.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as we've heard today.", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is the big cats,", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's the plankton.", "start": 51.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Two weeks ago, I was in Bangalore in India.", "start": 54.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was so privileged", "start": 57.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be able to teach in a hospice", "start": 59.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on the outskirts of Bangalore.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And early in the morning,", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I went into the ward.", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In that hospice,", "start": 68.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there were 31 men and women", "start": 70.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who were actively dying.", "start": 72.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I walked up to the bedside", "start": 74.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of an old woman", "start": 76.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who was breathing very rapidly, fragile,", "start": 78.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "obviously in the latter phase", "start": 81.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of active dying.", "start": 83.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I looked into her face.", "start": 86.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I looked into the face", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of her son sitting next to her,", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and his face was just riven", "start": 92.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with grief and confusion.", "start": 94.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I remembered", "start": 97.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a line from the Mahabharata,", "start": 100.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the great Indian epic:", "start": 103.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"What is the most wondrous thing in the world, Yudhisthira?\"", "start": 106.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "And Yudhisthira replied,", "start": 111.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"The most wondrous thing in the world", "start": 113.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that all around us", "start": 116.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "people can be dying", "start": 119.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we don't realize", "start": 121.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it can happen to us.\"", "start": 123.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I looked up.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Tending those 31 dying people", "start": 137.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were young women", "start": 140.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from villages around Bangalore.", "start": 142.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I looked into the face of one of these women,", "start": 144.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and I saw in her face", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the strength that arises", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when natural compassion is really present.", "start": 152.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I watched her hands", "start": 155.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as she bathed an old man.", "start": 157.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "My gaze went to another young woman", "start": 161.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "as she wiped the face", "start": 165.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of another dying person.", "start": 168.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it reminded me", "start": 170.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of something that I had just been present for.", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Every year or so,", "start": 174.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I have the privilege of taking clinicians", "start": 176.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the Himalayas and the Tibetan Plateau.", "start": 178.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And we run clinics", "start": 181.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in these very remote regions", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where there's no medical care whatsoever.", "start": 185.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And on the first day at Simikot in Humla,", "start": 188.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "far west of Nepal,", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the most impoverished region of Nepal,", "start": 194.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "an old man came in", "start": 197.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "clutching a bundle of rags.", "start": 199.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And he walked in, and somebody said something to him,", "start": 202.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we realized he was deaf,", "start": 205.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we looked into the rags,", "start": 207.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and there was this pair of eyes.", "start": 209.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The rags were unwrapped", "start": 212.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from a little girl", "start": 214.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "whose body was massively burned.", "start": 216.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Again,", "start": 221.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the eyes and hands", "start": 223.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of Avalokiteshvara.", "start": 225.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was the young women, the health aids,", "start": 227.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who cleaned the wounds of this baby", "start": 230.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and dressed the wounds.", "start": 233.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I know those hands and eyes;", "start": 235.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they touched me as well.", "start": 237.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They touched me at that time.", "start": 239.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have touched me throughout my 68 years.", "start": 241.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They touched me when I was four", "start": 244.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I lost my eyesight", "start": 246.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and was partially paralyzed.", "start": 248.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And my family brought in", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a woman whose mother had been a slave", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to take care of me.", "start": 254.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And that woman", "start": 257.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "did not have sentimental compassion.", "start": 259.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "She had phenomenal strength.", "start": 261.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it was really her strength, I believe,", "start": 264.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that became the kind of mudra and imprimatur", "start": 266.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that has been a guiding light in my life.", "start": 269.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So we can ask:", "start": 273.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What is compassion comprised of?", "start": 276.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And there are various facets.", "start": 280.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And there's referential and non-referential compassion.", "start": 282.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But first, compassion is comprised", "start": 285.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of that capacity", "start": 287.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to see clearly", "start": 289.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the nature of suffering.", "start": 291.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is that ability", "start": 293.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to really stand strong", "start": 295.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to recognize also", "start": 297.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I'm not separate from this suffering.", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But that is not enough,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because compassion,", "start": 303.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which activates the motor cortex,", "start": 305.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "means that we aspire,", "start": 307.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we actually aspire to transform suffering.", "start": 310.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And if we're so blessed,", "start": 313.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we engage in activities", "start": 315.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that transform suffering.", "start": 317.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But compassion has another component,", "start": 319.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that component is really essential.", "start": 321.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That component", "start": 324.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that we cannot be attached to outcome.", "start": 326.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now I worked with dying people", "start": 329.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for over 40 years.", "start": 332.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I had the privilege of working on death row", "start": 335.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in a maximum security [prison] for six years.", "start": 338.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I realized so clearly", "start": 341.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in bringing my own life experience,", "start": 343.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from working with dying people", "start": 345.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and training caregivers,", "start": 347.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that any attachment to outcome", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would distort deeply", "start": 352.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "my own capacity to be fully present", "start": 354.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the whole catastrophe.", "start": 357.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And when I worked in the prison system,", "start": 360.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it was so clear to me, this:", "start": 362.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that many of us", "start": 365.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in this room,", "start": 367.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and almost all of the men that I worked with on death row,", "start": 369.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the seeds of their own compassion had never been watered.", "start": 372.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That compassion is actually", "start": 375.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an inherent human quality.", "start": 377.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It is there within every human being.", "start": 380.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But the conditions", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for compassion to be activated,", "start": 385.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to be aroused,", "start": 389.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are particular conditions.", "start": 391.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I had that condition, to a certain extent,", "start": 393.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from my own childhood illness.", "start": 396.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Eve Ensler, whom you'll hear later,", "start": 398.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has had that condition activated", "start": 401.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "amazingly in her", "start": 403.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "through the various waters of suffering", "start": 406.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that she has been through.", "start": 409.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And what is fascinating", "start": 412.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that compassion has enemies,", "start": 414.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and those enemies are things like pity,", "start": 417.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "moral outrage,", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "fear.", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And you know, we have a society, a world,", "start": 427.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that is paralyzed by fear.", "start": 430.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in that paralysis, of course,", "start": 433.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our capacity for compassion", "start": 435.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is also paralyzed.", "start": 437.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The very word terror", "start": 439.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is global.", "start": 441.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The very feeling of terror is global.", "start": 443.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So our work, in a certain way,", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is to address this imago,", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this kind of archetype", "start": 450.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that has pervaded the psyche", "start": 452.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of our entire globe.", "start": 454.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now we know from neuroscience", "start": 458.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that compassion has", "start": 461.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "some very extraordinary qualities.", "start": 463.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "For example:", "start": 465.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A person who is cultivating compassion,", "start": 467.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when they are in the presence of suffering,", "start": 470.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they feel that suffering a lot more", "start": 473.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than many other people do.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "However,", "start": 478.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they return to baseline a lot sooner.", "start": 480.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is called resilience.", "start": 483.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Many of us think that compassion drains us,", "start": 485.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but I promise you", "start": 488.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it is something that truly enlivens us.", "start": 490.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Another thing about compassion", "start": 493.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that it really enhances what's called neural integration.", "start": 495.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It hooks up all parts of the brain.", "start": 498.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Another, which has been discovered", "start": 502.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by various researchers", "start": 504.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at Emory and at Davis and so on,", "start": 506.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that compassion enhances our immune system.", "start": 509.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Hey,", "start": 514.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we live in a very noxious world.", "start": 516.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 518.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Most of us are shrinking", "start": 520.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the face of psycho-social and physical poisons,", "start": 522.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the toxins of our world.", "start": 525.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But compassion, the generation of compassion,", "start": 528.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "actually mobilizes", "start": 530.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "our immunity.", "start": 533.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You know, if compassion is so good for us,", "start": 536.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I have a question.", "start": 539.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why don't we train our children", "start": 543.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in compassion?", "start": 545.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 548.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "If compassion is so good for us,", "start": 553.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "why don't we train our health care providers in compassion", "start": 556.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "so that they can do what they're supposed to do,", "start": 560.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "which is to really transform suffering?", "start": 563.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And if compassion is so good for us,", "start": 566.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "why don't we vote on compassion?", "start": 569.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Why don't we vote for people in our government", "start": 573.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "based on compassion,", "start": 577.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so that we can have", "start": 579.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a more caring world?", "start": 581.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In Buddhism,", "start": 584.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we say, \"it takes a strong back and a soft front.\"", "start": 586.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It takes tremendous strength of the back", "start": 589.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to uphold yourself in the midst of conditions.", "start": 592.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And that is the mental quality of equanimity.", "start": 595.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But it also takes a soft front --", "start": 598.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the capacity to really be open to the world as it is,", "start": 601.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to have an undefended heart.", "start": 604.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the archetype of this in Buddhism", "start": 606.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is Avalokiteshvara, Kuan-Yin.", "start": 609.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a female archetype:", "start": 611.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "she who perceives", "start": 614.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the cries of suffering in the world.", "start": 616.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "She stands with 10,000 arms,", "start": 623.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and in every hand,", "start": 627.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is an instrument of liberation,", "start": 629.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and in the palm of every hand, there are eyes,", "start": 632.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and these are the eyes of wisdom.", "start": 635.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I say that, for thousands of years,", "start": 638.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "women have lived,", "start": 641.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "exemplified, met in intimacy,", "start": 643.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "the archetype of Avalokitesvara,", "start": 647.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of Kuan-Yin,", "start": 650.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "she who perceives", "start": 652.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the cries of suffering in the world.", "start": 654.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Women have manifested for thousands of years", "start": 657.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the strength arising from compassion", "start": 660.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "in an unfiltered, unmediated way", "start": 664.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in perceiving suffering", "start": 667.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as it is.", "start": 669.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have infused societies with kindness,", "start": 673.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and we have really felt that", "start": 676.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as woman after woman", "start": 678.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has stood on this stage", "start": 680.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the past day and a half.", "start": 682.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they have actualized compassion", "start": 685.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "through direct action.", "start": 687.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Jody Williams called it:", "start": 689.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's good to meditate.", "start": 691.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'm sorry, you've got to do a little bit of that, Jody.", "start": 693.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Step back, give your mother a break, okay.", "start": 696.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 699.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But the other side of the equation", "start": 701.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is you've got to come out of your cave.", "start": 703.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You have to come into the world", "start": 705.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like Asanga did,", "start": 707.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who was looking to realize Maitreya Buddha", "start": 709.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "after 12 years sitting in the cave.", "start": 712.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He said, \"I'm out of here.\"", "start": 715.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He's going down the path.", "start": 717.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He sees something in the path.", "start": 719.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He looks, it's a dog, he drops to his knees.", "start": 721.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He sees that the dog has this big wound on its leg.", "start": 724.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "The wound is just filled with maggots.", "start": 728.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He puts out his tongue", "start": 731.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in order to remove the maggots,", "start": 734.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so as not to harm them.", "start": 736.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And at that moment,", "start": 739.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the dog transformed", "start": 741.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the Buddha of love and kindness.", "start": 743.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I believe", "start": 747.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that women and girls today", "start": 749.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have to partner in a powerful way with men --", "start": 751.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "with their fathers,", "start": 755.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with their sons, with their brothers,", "start": 757.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with the plumbers, the road builders,", "start": 760.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the caregivers, the doctors, the lawyers,", "start": 762.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with our president,", "start": 765.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and with all beings.", "start": 767.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The women in this room", "start": 769.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are lotuses in a sea of fire.", "start": 771.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "May we actualize that capacity", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for women everywhere.", "start": 776.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 778.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 780.26, "duration": 12.0}]